cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SY, cs.CV. 

The paper proposes a practical Thompson sampling based RL algorithm for efficient exploration in high dimensions. The algorithm is applied to a range of Atari games in Arcade Learning Environments. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also involves Bayesian Linear Regression (BLR) model, which falls under the sub-category cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the application of the algorithm to Atari games involves computer vision, which falls under the sub-category cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
